%% Diagram: Hedged request timing (Tail at Scale, Dean & Barroso)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant R1 as Replica A
    participant R2 as Replica B

    Note over C: Wait until t = ~p95 of expected latency
    C->>R1: Request (primary)
    Note over R1: Slow path (in tail)
    Note over C: Timer fires at p95
    C->>R2: Hedged request (same payload)
    R2-->>C: Response (fast path)
    Note over C: Use fastest reply,<br/>cancel the loser
    C-->>R1: Cancel (or ignore late reply)
    Note over C,R2: Tail-latency p99 bounded by<br/>min of two replica latencies
